    <statement>
      <p>Design functions to help solve the following problem. Use the answer guidelines in <xref text="title" ref="program-design_exercises_introduction"/>.</p>
      <p>We have a string containing two cards of a hand in blackjack, like <c>"KH 7D"</c> (the king of hearts and the seven of diamonds) or <c>"AS 9C"</c> (the ace of spades and the nine of clubs). We want to compute the total value of the hand. The king, queen, and jack are worth 10 points each. The ace is worth either 1 point or 11 points, whichever is more favorable to the hand without going over 21. All other cards are worth their numeric value.</p>
